\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. R. orientalis} (Müller Arg.) Boiss.,{\i  Fl. Or.}{\b  1}: 427 (1867). Annual 20-70 cm. Lower leaves up to 100 × 11 mm, oblanceolate, obtuse, petiolate; the upper pinnatifid with 1 or 2 pairs of lobes, the lobes mostly 1·5-3·5 mm wide, ovate-lanceolate to linear. Sepals 3-4·5 mm; petals like those of {\b 15} but 3-3·5 mm. Capsule 7-13 × 5-6 mm, nodding, ovoid or obovoid.{\i  S.E. Greece} ({\i Salamis}); {\i W. Kriti }({\i Gavdhos}). Cr Gr.
