\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. R. stricta} Pers.,{\i  Syn. Pl. }{\b 2}: 10 (1806). Biennial; stems 30-50 cm, erect, with long, erect branches. Leaves with 1 or 2 pairs of often bifid pinnae; segments up to 6 mm wide. Bracts caducous; pedicels filiform; flowers pendent. Sepals 1-1·5 mm, ovate; petals 2-3 mm, yellow; limb of the upper shorter than the claw, 5-partite, of the lower bilobed, with lobes 1- or 2-lobulate at the base. Capsule 7-16 mm, erect, obovoid or cylindrical. 2n = 24.{\i  Gypsaceous soils. E. & C..Spain.} Hs.
